	<section id="intro">

      <h1>Introduction</h1>
      <hr>

      <h4>Mixture supports publishing to Amazon S3 for static Mixture projects.</h4>
      <p>To begin you simply need to create an Amazon AWS account (if you don't already have one) and then create a new bucket. It's best to name the bucket as the domain you wish to use (eg. mysite.com), make sure you give the correct access rights to the bucket and set it up in the preferences for static website hosting.</p>
      <p>You can read more about the Amazon setup process <a href="http://www.smalldatajournalism.com/projects/one-offs/using-amazon-s3/">from this great guide</a>.</p>

    </section>

    <section id="settings" style="min-height: 98px;">

      <h1>Settings</h1>
      <hr>
      <p>One you have setup your Amazon bucket, simply create a json file in the root of your project called <code>.s3settings</code> and add the following with your Amazon details:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>accessKey</code> your Amazon access key</li>
        <li><code>secretKey</code> your Amazon secret key</li>
        <li><code>bucket</code> your Amazon bucket</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Example settings:</p>
      <pre class="prettyprint linenums pad" data-initialized="true" data-gclp-id="0"><ol class="linenums"><li class="L0"><span class="pun">{</span></li><li class="L1"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"accessKey"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="str">"your-key"</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L2"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"secretKey"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="str">"your-secret-key"</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L3"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"bucket"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="str">"your-bucket"</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L4"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"region"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="str">"your-region"</span></li><li class="L5"><span class="pun">}</span></li></ol></pre>
      <p>Thats it, you're all set - simply convert to HTML within the Mixture tools and click the Amazon S3 button to publish!</p>

